      • addToDuration

        public void addToDuration(double d)
        Creates a DurationModifier to add a value to each duration.

        Uses the modifyDurations method.

        Fires a TimeSeries.MODIFIED property change event, with this as the new value and no old value. Same as doing this: 

         
  
        DurationModifier dm = new DurationModifier(Operation.ADD, d);
        ts.map(dm);
        Parameters:
        d - an amount to add
        See Also:
        DurationModifier

      • map

        public void map(TimedModifier mod)
        map is the GoF visitor(331) design pattern. It loops through all the TimeEvent and applies the modifier to each event. Sort of like mapcar in LISP (but Java does not have lambdas so you need the TimeEventModifier interface).

        Fires a TimeSeries.MODIFIED property change event, with this as the new value and no old value. 

         TimeSeries series = new TimeSeries();
 TimeEvent e = new TimeEvent(1,2);
 series.add(e);
 series.map(new DurationModifier(1d, TimeEventModifier.Operation.ADD));
        Parameters:
        mod - a TimeEventModifier implementation.
        See Also:
        StartBeatModifier

      • map

        public void map(TimedModifier mod,
       double after)
        map calls map(TimeEventModifier) only if the note's start beat is after the specified value.

        Fires a TimeSeries.MODIFIED property change event, with this as the new value and no old value.

        Parameters:
        mod - a TimeEventModifier implementation.
        after - a double value. Modify notes only after this start beat.
